{
    "ocr_text": "Mr. Hugh Prynne,
Organizer A. F. of L.,
25 3rd Ave., New York City.

Dear Sir and Brother:

I would like you to meet me at the Victoria Hotel at 9:30 Saturday morning prepared to accompany me to Siegel Cooper Co.'s office where I have an appointment with Mr. Greenhut at ten o'clock. I trust you have no other engagement which will interfere as this is a most important matter.

Anticipating our early meeting, I am,
Fraternally yours,

President
American Federation of Labor.",
